@node "1st_Season_PK" "Star Trek First Season Promotional Kit  "

                           @{fg shine}BRIEF CASE PRESS KIT@{fg text}

 @{b}DESCRIPTION:@{ub}

       The first season press kit is enclosed in an aluminum halliburton
       flight case and consists of the following items.

       @{b}@{i}FOLDER -GENERAL INFORMATION-@{ub}@{ui}

       Rolodex card

       1 page describing the items included in the kit

       1 page explaining that the radio promos aren't ready yet and will be
       sent at a later date.

       2 page press release entitled "Star Trek:TNG Premiers Intergalactic
       Adventures on (DATE) on (CALL LETTERS), Channel (#)

       2 pages entitled "THE USS Enterprise (NCC-1701D) FACTS"

       2 pages entitled "The USS Enterprise (NCC-1701-D)

       2 Pages entitled "Star Trek: The Next Generation" includes a brief
       series description and 4-5 lines of biographies for each of the cast.

       3 pages entitled "Continuing the Legend of the Original Series
       Star Trek: TNG Beams onto American TV"

       2 pages entitled "Star Trek: TNG Story Ideas & Tip Sheet"

       1 page entitled "Star Trek Background"

       @{b}@{i}FOLDER -PRESS RELEASES, BIOGRAPHIES AND CREDITS-@{ub}@{ui}

       2 pages of biographys for EACH cast member

       2 pages of quotes from EACH cast member

       2 pages of a Gene Roddenberry biography

       2 pages of Gene Roddenberry quotes

       2 pages of a Robert H. Justman biography


      @{b}@{i} FOLDER -PROMOTION & PUBLICITY STRATEGIES-@{ub}@{ui}

       4 pages entitled "Promotional Strategies - Media Recommendations"

       1 page entitled "Promotional Strategies - Demographics"

       2 pages entitled "Promotional Opportunities - An Overview"


       @{b}@{i}FOLDER -PHOTOS & SLIDES-@{ub}@{ui}

       12 Slides enclosed in plastic

       1 Slide of TNG Logo in plastic

       1 b/w photo of crew vertical

       1 b/w photo of Patrick Stewart

       1 b/w photo of Jonathan Frakes beardless

       1 b/w photo of Levar Burton

       1 b/w photo of Denise Crosby

       1 b/w photo of Michael Dorn

       1 b/w photo of Gates McFadden

       1 b/w photo of Marina Sirtis

       1 b/w photo of Brent Spiner

       1 b/w photo of Wil Wheaton

       1 b/w photo of various scenes from Encounter at Farpoint

       1 b/w photo of Enterprise head on


       @{b}@{i}FOLDER -PRINT ADS AND ELEMENTS-@{ub}@{ui}

       4 Reaction photos (There may have been more originally)

       19 TV Guide ad slicks (Could also have been more)


      @{b}@{i} FOLDER -Synopsys-@{ub}@{ui}

       Synopsis for Episode #721 Encounter at Farpoint

       Synopsis for Episode #103 The Naked Now

       Synopsis for Episode #104 Code of Honor

       Synopsis for Episode #105 Haven

       Synopsis for Episode #106 Where None Have Gone Before

       Air schedule for showing the following episodes; 721, 103, 104, 107,
       106, 108, 109, 110, 111, 105 (This was later revised and the order
       of episodes was changed)

       With the exception of episode #721, the episodical photos were sent
       at a later date.


       @{b}@{i}2 THREE QUARTER INCH VIDEO TAPES@{ub}@{ui}

       One tape entitled "Electronic Press Kit." Length 41 minutes.
       Includes log in tape case. The other tape consists of 5 TV
       promotional spots. Two are thirty seconds and three are ten seconds.


      @{b}@{i} MISC@{ub}@{ui}

       1 Digital Clock

       1 heavy pewter ensignia pen

       * ALL ITEMS ARE COPYRIGHT 1987


       @{b}VALUE:@{ub} $500 - $1500 depending on condition and contents.
@endnode

